From: nerves_system_openwrt_one
Subject: [PATCH] arm64: dts: mt7981b-openwrt-one: full board peripheral support

Replace the minimal mainline mt7981b.dtsi and mt7981b-openwrt-one.dts
with the OpenWrt 24.10 versions including SPI NAND on &spi0 (using
OpenWrt's spi-mt65xx + SPI calibration patches), both Ethernets, WiFi
with nvmem calibration, LEDs, buttons, RTC, watchdog, and the full
peripheral set. Linux 6.18 mainline still ships only a 15-line stub
for the OpenWRT One.

